name: slice::<impl [T]>::fill_with

option::Option: Unknown([Downcast(VariantIdx(1, ThreadLocalIndex)), Field(0, Ty { id: 1178, kind: RigidTy(Ref(Region { kind: ReErased }, Ty { id: 95, kind: Param(ParamTy { index: 0, name: "T" }) }, Mut)) })])

doc:
Fills `self` with elements returned by calling a closure repeatedly.

 This method uses a closure to create new values. If you'd rather
 [`Clone`] a given value, use [`fill`]. If you want to use the [`Default`]
 trait to generate values, you can pass [`Default::default`] as the
 argument.

 [`fill`]: slice::fill

 # Examples

 ```
 let mut buf = vec![1; 10];
 buf.fill_with(Default::default);
 assert_eq!(buf, vec![0; 10]);
 ```
